d largely unknown or inaccessible to most researchers, provides a platform for John Pilcher as a writer and distinguished scholar-diplomat.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEconomic history. 0aJapan -- Economic conditions -- 1945-1989. 0aJapan -- Economic policy -- 1945-1989. 0aJapan -- Foreign relations -- 1945-1989. 4aAsian Studies. 4aBiography: historical, political and military. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aHistory. 4aInternational Relations. 4aJapan. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aWhitehall.  areports to uk government.  auk-japan relations.1 aCortazzi, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCortazzi, Hugh, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNish, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorbury, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066278840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781898823285?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781898823285423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781898823285/original  a978-3-11-066278-8  Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK